4 I discovered this little gem while at a client in downtown Phoenix.  As with most hidden secrets in the area, this place is situated in a nondescript old house and is very easy to pass by if you aren't looking for it.  Although I've only tried one dish there, the menu is a mix of Asian delights from Indian to Vietnamese to Chinese.  I recommend anything with curry, as they have what is probably the best yellow curry sauce I have ever tasted.  I ordered mine with chicken but you can easily have a vegetarian version made, and from what my vegetarian friend told me it was just as great.  If you are one of those office types grinding away in a downtown phoenix building slowly losing your soul, do yourself a favor and drive a few blocks north and check the place out.  It sure beats walking to Subway or Quizno's for lunch every day.
